<br>
As a Theurgist it hardly matters as they are about the only caster that is better off tri-specing to around 30 in all three lines anyway, than just solo-speccing one line to 50, as some Wizards, Runemasters and Eldritches do.<br>
<br>
For me, it's all about Earth.  At 22nd, I'm still killing red Cornish Hunters with 70% of my Power, and I've been killing groups of mobs for the group exp bonuses forever.  At lower levels, the bandit camps are just amazing experience, you target the named leader in the center of the camp, spam every pet at him and just back off.  You get good experience for him, and sometimes up to a 50% bonus for the huge groups of blue, green and grey bandits who try to 'help.'<br>
<br>
By 22nd, I am getting into groups with 36th level people and just chain-casting my bladeturn spells on the main tank during combat.  It saves the Cleric tons of power and allows me to contribute even though the stuff we are facing is red and purple to the mid-30's groupmates...<br>
<br>
But each line has its features.<br>
<br>
A solid ice-Spec and you can Snare, Root, Blast almost as well as a Wizard, although the pet-spamming becomes dangerous (since the pets don't run up and aggro the mobs, they stand close to you and nuke with Ice Blasts...).<br>
<br>
I'm not real clear on the effectiveness of a heavy Air Spec, and with the recent Stun changes, I wouldn't reccomend it right now.<br>
